<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Combined length of head, pronotum and elytra = 1.7-2.1 mm; maximal pronotal width = 0.9-1.3 mm. Body (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 19–21" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 19 - 21. Megarthrus panda sp. nov.: habitus, male: dorsal 19 ventral 20, and lateral 21 views. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures19-21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578547" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">19-21</figureCitation>
) predominantly chestnut brown, with pronotum usually slightly paler, frons slightly paler than vertex, and legs slightly paler than elytra. Anterior frontal margin slightly carinate, evenly convex in dorsal view. Antenna as in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 33–40" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figures 33 - 40. Megarthrus panda sp. nov., female genital segments, dorsal part in ventral view 33 and ventral part in dorsal 34 and lateral 35 views antenna 36 female tergite VIII in lateral 37 and dorsal 38 views male left hemitergite IX 39 female sternite VIII in ventral view 40. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures33-40" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578550" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">36</figureCitation>
. Prothorax as in Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 22–23" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figures 22 - 23. Megarthrus panda sp. nov., prothorax in dorsal 22 and ventral 23 views. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures22-23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578548" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">22</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 22–23" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figures 22 - 23. Megarthrus panda sp. nov., prothorax in dorsal 22 and ventral 23 views. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures22-23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578548" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">23</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures19-21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578547" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" start="Figures 19–21" startId="F5">
