<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Male</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Protibia fairly straight and evenly expanding from base to apex; adventral side flattened. Mesotrochanter (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 24–32" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 24 - 32. Megarthrus panda sp. nov., aedeagus in ventral 24 and lateral 25 views; metatibiae 26 mesotibiae 27 mesotrochanter and mesofemur 28 metatrochanter and metafemur 29 tergite VIII in lateral 30 and ventral 31 views sternite VIII in ventral view 32. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures24-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578549" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">28</figureCitation>
) with about twenty peg-like setae grouped as a field. Mesofemur (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 24–32" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 24 - 32. Megarthrus panda sp. nov., aedeagus in ventral 24 and lateral 25 views; metatibiae 26 mesotibiae 27 mesotrochanter and mesofemur 28 metatrochanter and metafemur 29 tergite VIII in lateral 30 and ventral 31 views sternite VIII in ventral view 32. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures24-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578549" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">28</figureCitation>
) slightly arcuate and slightly swollen. Mesotibia (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 24–32" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 24 - 32. Megarthrus panda sp. nov., aedeagus in ventral 24 and lateral 25 views; metatibiae 26 mesotibiae 27 mesotrochanter and mesofemur 28 metatrochanter and metafemur 29 tergite VIII in lateral 30 and ventral 31 views sternite VIII in ventral view 32. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures24-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578549" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">27</figureCitation>
) subangulate, bearing peg-like setae arranged in two rows. Metatrochanter and metafemur (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 24–32" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 24 - 32. Megarthrus panda sp. nov., aedeagus in ventral 24 and lateral 25 views; metatibiae 26 mesotibiae 27 mesotrochanter and mesofemur 28 metatrochanter and metafemur 29 tergite VIII in lateral 30 and ventral 31 views sternite VIII in ventral view 32. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures24-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578549" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">29</figureCitation>
) markedly swollen; posterior margin of metatrochanter broadly rectangular; posterior margin of metafemur concave in ventral view, forming sharp ridge on half length. Metatibia (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 24–32" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 24 - 32. Megarthrus panda sp. nov., aedeagus in ventral 24 and lateral 25 views; metatibiae 26 mesotibiae 27 mesotrochanter and mesofemur 28 metatrochanter and metafemur 29 tergite VIII in lateral 30 and ventral 31 views sternite VIII in ventral view 32. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures24-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578549" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">26</figureCitation>
) swollen, with adventral side flattened and broadly emarginated on apical two-thirds; metatibial peg-like setae grouped as a field on apical quarter with additional peg-like setae arranged in scattered row bordering each side of emargination. Abdominal tergite VIII as in Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 24–32" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 24 - 32. Megarthrus panda sp. nov., aedeagus in ventral 24 and lateral 25 views; metatibiae 26 mesotibiae 27 mesotrochanter and mesofemur 28 metatrochanter and metafemur 29 tergite VIII in lateral 30 and ventral 31 views sternite VIII in ventral view 32. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures24-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578549" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">30</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 24–32" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 24 - 32. Megarthrus panda sp. nov., aedeagus in ventral 24 and lateral 25 views; metatibiae 26 mesotibiae 27 mesotrochanter and mesofemur 28 metatrochanter and metafemur 29 tergite VIII in lateral 30 and ventral 31 views sternite VIII in ventral view 32. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures24-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578549" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">31</figureCitation>
; abdominal sternite VIII in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 24–32" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 24 - 32. Megarthrus panda sp. nov., aedeagus in ventral 24 and lateral 25 views; metatibiae 26 mesotibiae 27 mesotrochanter and mesofemur 28 metatrochanter and metafemur 29 tergite VIII in lateral 30 and ventral 31 views sternite VIII in ventral view 32. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures24-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578549" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">32</figureCitation>
; hemitergites IX as in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 33–40" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figures 33 - 40. Megarthrus panda sp. nov., female genital segments, dorsal part in ventral view 33 and ventral part in dorsal 34 and lateral 35 views antenna 36 female tergite VIII in lateral 37 and dorsal 38 views male left hemitergite IX 39 female sternite VIII in ventral view 40. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures33-40" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578550" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">39</figureCitation>
. Aedeagus (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 24–32" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 24 - 32. Megarthrus panda sp. nov., aedeagus in ventral 24 and lateral 25 views; metatibiae 26 mesotibiae 27 mesotrochanter and mesofemur 28 metatrochanter and metafemur 29 tergite VIII in lateral 30 and ventral 31 views sternite VIII in ventral view 32. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures24-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578549" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">24</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 24–32" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 24 - 32. Megarthrus panda sp. nov., aedeagus in ventral 24 and lateral 25 views; metatibiae 26 mesotibiae 27 mesotrochanter and mesofemur 28 metatrochanter and metafemur 29 tergite VIII in lateral 30 and ventral 31 views sternite VIII in ventral view 32. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1056.66553.figures24-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/578549" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">25</figureCitation>
) with ventral wall strongly narrowed at apical third in ventral view, with ventral outline markedly sinuate to slender apex strongly recurved ventrally in lateral view.
</paragraph>
