<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liu &amp; Cuccodoro" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megarthrus panda" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panda">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Megarthrus panda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. shares the main body color and the forested mountains of Yunnan Province with its eponymous mammal the small 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liu &amp; Cuccodoro" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megarthrus panda" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panda">Megarthrus panda</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="F. G. Cuvier" authorityYear="1825" class="Mammalia" family="Ailuridae" genus="Ailurus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ailurus fulgens" order="Carnivora" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fulgens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Ailurus fulgens</emphasis>
